METHOD.
Participants.
A total number of 200 participants made up of 87 males and 113 females between the age of 29-51 years of age where selected. The mean age was 35 and standard deviation of 8.35.
The participants were selected making use of available sample from population of primary and secondary school teachers in Enugu-East Local Government Area of Enugu State. There are total number of 62 registered secondary schools and 103 registered primary schools in Enugu-East Local Government. From the total number of registered schools in the LGA, I was able to select teachers from 3 primary schools and 7 secondary schools using convenience sampling method. Thus, among the available samples, I selected those schools that are closer to me and where I have friends working as teachers.
.
Instruments.

